worksheet.stem:
Use the function obtained above to calculate the Frobenius norm of an m×n matrix with the following script:

 

A = [5 7 9; 1 8 4; 7 6 2];
Fn = Fnorm (A)

(Round the final answer to four decimal places.)

 

The Frobenius norm of an m×n matrix is __A__.
worksheet.commonFeedback:
Function

 

function Norm = Fnorm(x)
[n,m] = size(x);
for i = 1:n
[xm,j] = max(abs(x(i,:)));
  xn(i,:) = x(i,:)/x(i,j);
end
s = 0;
for i = 1:n
  for j = 1:m
    s = s + x(i,j)^2;
  end
end

 

Script

 

 clear, clc, format compact
 A = [5 7 9; 1 8 4; 7 6 2];
 Fn = Fnorm(A)
>> Norm=sqrt(s);

 

Output

 

Fn =
    18.0278

sectionBreak.stem:
The given figure shows a statically determinate truss. This type of structure can be described as a system of coupled linear algebraic equations by developing free-body force diagrams for the forces at each node in the given figure. The sum of the forces in both the horizontal and the vertical directions must be zero at each node because the system is at rest.

Therefore, for node 1

For node 2

For node 3

%media:formula28.mml%

 

where Fi,h is the external horizontal force applied to node i (where a positive force is applied from left to right) and F1,v is the external vertical force applied to node i (where a positive force is applied upward). Thus, in this problem, the 1000-N downward force on node 1 corresponds to F1,v = −1000 N. For this case, all other Fi,v ’s and Fi,h’s are zero. Note that the directions of the internal forces and reactions are unknown. The proper application of Newton’s laws requires only consistent assumptions regarding direction. Solutions are negative if the directions are assumed incorrectly. Also note that in this problem, the forces in all members are assumed to be in tension and act to pull adjoining nodes together. A negative solution therefore corresponds to compression. When the external forces are substituted and the trigonometric functions are evaluated, this problem reduces to a set of six linear algebraic equations with six unknowns.

Determine the change in the reactions at the two supports if the force at the peak is directed upward. (Round the final answer to the nearest whole number.)

 

The solution is __a__.
worksheet.commonFeedback: Note that the horizontal reactions (H2 = –1200) and the vertical reactions (V2 + V3 = 146.4102 + 953.5898 = 1100) are equal to the negative of the imposed loads. This is a good check that the computation is correct.
